&nbsp;&nbsp;


  <p class="">In 1932, Julia Lawrence Terry founded New Eyes with foresight (no pun intended!), determonation and a spirit of generosity. This past year, we happened upon some old tapes in the basement of the New Eyes building and a volunteer cleaned them up and remastered them. To our delight, it was a radio interview of Mrs. Terry - and the first time we ever heard her in her own voice! </p><p class="">On this last day of Women’s History Month, we wanted to share it with you: </p>





















  
  



&nbsp;]]></description><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/53628c55e4b038197f765c8d/1680296424172-HPEBXR016DP4WJERZCI4/NE+-+Women%27s+History+Month.png?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1037" height="695"><media:title type="plain">Closing out Women's History Month with a Word From Mrs. Terry</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>The Cost of Glasses is Too Darn High</title><dc:creator>Jean Gajano</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 06 Mar 2023 20:53:01 +0000</pubDate><link>https://new-eyes.org/blog/too-high</link><guid isPermaLink="false">53628c55e4b038197f765c8d:5d8116ef505a1b02b25ed591:640647826257af12558dba9c</guid><description><![CDATA[&nbsp;










































  

    
  
    

      

      
